There are three ways to utilize Netflix:
;[[#Using_Chromium|Using the Chromium web browser]]:Simple and using newer HTML5 approach in the OSS browser.
;[[#Using_Google_Chrome|Using the Google Chrome web browser]]:Simple and using newer HTML5 approach, but ''at this time'' requires this particular, binary-only browser.
;[[Netflix/Pipelight|Using Pipelight]]:A little more involved and using the Silverlight status quo, but slightly more robust and versatile without being limited to one browser.

==Using Chromium==

Enable the <code>widevine</code> USE flag for <code>www-client/chromium</code>, as well as <code>www-plugins/chrome-binary-plugins</code>:

{{rootCmd|<nowiki>echo -e 'www-plugins/chrome-binary-plugins widevine\nwww-client/chromium widevine' >> /etc/portage/package.use</nowiki>}}

Emerge these two packages:

{{rootCmd|<nowiki>emerge www-plugins/chrome-binary-pluginswww-client/chromium</nowiki>}}

From there it should work flawlessly.

==Using Google Chrome==

Emerge Google Chrome:
{{rootCmd|emerge -atv google-chrome}}

===Troubleshooting===

In Netflix settings, 'Your Account > YOUR PROFILE > Playback Settings', ensure that 'Prefer HTML5 player instead of Silverlight' is checked (should be by default).

